.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/implementation-summary.md:34:# Implementation Summary: Compiled Routing Default-On Safe Cutover
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/implementation-summary.md:38:<!-- HVR_REFERENCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/references/hvr-rules.md -->
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/implementation-summary.md:47:| **Status** | Ruling settled (adopt the phased path P0->P4, decided on the analysis; reversible and operator-overridable). No runtime implementation started; a separate operator go-ahead gates P0. |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/implementation-summary.md:50:| **Runtime change** | None authored by this documentation phase |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/implementation-summary.md:51:| **Repository default** | Unchanged; compiled routing remains default-off |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/implementation-summary.md:60:The decision packet settles the ruling on the analysis: adopt a staged path to compiled routing as the effective default rather than flipping the default now. No runtime work has begun. The current live integration remains additive metadata only, the compiled and legacy decisions remain identical, and the repository flag remains off by default. The operator may override the ruling to flip-now at any time; that override is available but not blocking.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/implementation-summary.md:62:The planned program starts by documenting and observing the existing behavior, then adds drift enforcement, a bounded canary, data-driven eligibility, and finally a reversible hub-by-hub default change. The three benchmark scorer files remain pinned throughout.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/implementation-summary.md:70:### P0: Governance, Observability, and Resolver Stability
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/implementation-summary.md:72:Document the environment flag, distinguish drift-to-legacy from resolver breakage, expose serving status per hub, and remove or explicitly guard the runtime dependency on a spec-tree path.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/implementation-summary.md:74:### P1 and P2: Enforcement and Canary
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/implementation-summary.md:76:Add re-mint-required CI for stale manifests, then enable compiled routing in one named environment profile while the repository default remains off.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/implementation-summary.md:78:### P3 and P4: Eligibility and Effective Default
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/implementation-summary.md:80:Derive both eligibility consumers from the manifest-freshness rule already owned by `decision-record.md`, then stage the global default one hub at a time while preserving `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING=0` as the fleet-wide kill-switch.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/implementation-summary.md:82:No runtime file, environment profile, manifest, CI job, hub directive, or frozen scorer file was changed while authoring this record.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/implementation-summary.md:90:Delivery follows the ordered gates in `plan.md`: an operator go-ahead to begin, P0 safety surface, P1 drift enforcement, P2 canary, P3 derived eligibility, and P4 staged cutover. Each stage records parity, status, rollback, and scorer-integrity evidence before the next stage can begin. The implementation stops at the first failed gate.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/implementation-summary.md:102:| Treat global default-on as the P4 outcome | Accepted | No default change before P0-P3 evidence |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/implementation-summary.md:103:| Derive eligibility from a valid fresh manifest | Accepted (implemented in P3) | Future onboarding and both runtime consumers share one rule |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/implementation-summary.md:104:| Promote the resolver to a stable runtime path | Accepted (implemented in P0) | Spec-tree renames stop being a silent runtime drift source |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/implementation-summary.md:114:| Keep the repository default off during documentation, drift CI, and the canary | The current compiled path changes no routing decisions, so safety and observability must land before the default carries operational weight. |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/implementation-summary.md:115:| Pin the three scorer files at every stage | The parity baseline must stay stable while the harness around it evolves. |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/implementation-summary.md:116:| Keep rollback stage-local | A failed canary or eligibility change should not discard earlier governance and diagnostic improvements. |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/implementation-summary.md:117:| Make sibling packets consume these contracts | One authoritative fallback and eligibility definition prevents create-skill and benchmark behavior from diverging. |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/implementation-summary.md:127:| Ruling (ADR-001) | Settled: adopt the phased path, decided on the analysis; operator override to flip-now remains available |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/implementation-summary.md:128:| Runtime implementation tests | Planned; no runtime implementation exists in this phase |
