.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:2:title: "Decision Record: Compiled Routing Default-On"
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:3:description: "Three decisions governing whether and how SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING becomes the repo's effective default: defer global default-on to a staged P4 outcome, single-source compiled eligibility to a valid fresh manifest, and remediate the runtime-to-spec-tree resolver coupling."
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:5:  - "compiled routing default-on decision record"
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:12:    packet_pointer: "sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision"
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:15:    recent_action: "Settled ADR-001 on the analysis to adopt the phased path"
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:16:    next_safe_action: "Begin P0 on operator go-ahead"
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:28:      - "Flip the default now or adopt the phased path? Adopt the phased path (ADR-001), settled on the analysis; operator may override."
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:31:# Decision Record: Compiled Routing Default-On
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:35:<!-- HVR_REFERENCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/references/hvr-rules.md -->
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:40:## ADR-001: Defer global default-on to a staged P4 outcome
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:46:| **Status** | Accepted: adopt the phased path (settled on the fresh-Opus analysis and source verification per the session directive; reversible; operator may override to flip-now) |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:48:| **Deciders** | Claude Opus 4.8 (settled on the analysis, per the session directive to settle the decision), independent fresh-Opus review (the dissent this ruling adopts); operator retains override authority |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:55:The parent goal asks to make compiled routing the effective default, framing it as flipping `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING` from off to on. Reading the live integration point shows that framing buys nothing and costs real surface. The advisor enters compiled routing only through `enrichCompiledRoutes()` at `advisor-recommend.ts:357`. With the flag unset that function returns its input untouched (`:362`). With the flag set it maps over recommendations the legacy path already computed and attaches `compiledRoute` as an additive sibling field, `{ ...recommendation, compiledRoute }` at `:371`, and never recomputes the chosen `skillId` or `workflowMode`. Turning the flag on can only make that extra field appear or, on drift, silently not appear. It cannot change which skill is recommended.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:57:The sibling `011-runtime-engine` already flipped all seven hubs' manifests to `servingAuthority: compiled`, held inert behind the default-off flag. So the destination machinery exists. What does not exist is the reason to flip: today the flip is behavior-neutral by construction.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:62:- The three frozen benchmark scorer files (`router-replay.cjs`, `score-skill-benchmark.cjs`, `load-playbook-scenarios.cjs`) are pinned and never edited.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:63:- `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING` is absent from `ENV-REFERENCE.md`, which CLAUDE.md section 6 mandates as the source of truth for flag defaults. Flipping an undocumented flag violates that mandate.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:64:- The serve-time shim recomputes each hub's decision from live config and falls back to a `{ servingAuthority: "legacy" }` sentinel on any mismatch (`compiled-route.cjs:36-39`), which the advisor maps to `undefined` (`advisor-recommend.ts:351`). Editing a hub reverts it to legacy until re-minted, with nothing to observe the reversion.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:73:**We chose**: Treat global default-on as the final outcome of a four-step program (P0 through P4), not a one-line default change made now.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:75:**How it works**: P0 documents the flag in `ENV-REFERENCE.md` and makes the verify harness distinguish drift-to-legacy from breakage plus a per-hub serving-status readout. P1 adds a drift-detection CI that recomputes each hub's live hash against its minted manifest and fails re-mint-required. P2 canaries default-on in one env profile while the repo default stays off. P3 replaces the two hardcoded allowlists with a data-driven eligibility rule (see ADR-002). P4 flips the repo default hub-by-hub, keeping `=0` as the documented kill-switch. The flip becomes worthwhile precisely when compiled routing does something legacy cannot (a consumed decision, a caught drift), which P0 through P3 create.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:77:**Settlement**: This ruling is settled on the merits of the analysis above (the five premise-failures and the resolver coupling), as the session directive to settle the decision using the fresh-Opus analysis requires. It is a reversible documentation decision: no runtime change follows from it, and the operator may override to flip-now at any time. Acceptance settles the sequencing (phased) only; a separate operator go-ahead gates the start of P0 implementation.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:88:| **Phased P0 to P4 (chosen)** | Reversible at every step; drift caught by CI not production; flag documented before it is load-bearing; the flip lands when it carries benefit | Four phases of enabling work before the headline default flips | 9/10 |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:89:| Flip the repo default now | One-line change; matches the literal goal wording | Zero routing benefit (additive metadata only); normalizes silent drift; inverts the kill-switch (absence becomes compiled); violates the ENV-REFERENCE governance mandate | 3/10 |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:90:| Abandon compiled routing | Removes the drift surface entirely | Discards a built, proven, reversible system and the parity work behind it; loses the future benefit the phased path unlocks | 2/10 |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:92:**Why this one**: The destination (compiled as the effective default) is not rejected, it is sequenced. Flipping today trades governance and observability surface for a benefit that is currently zero, so the correct move is to build the benefit and the safety net first, then flip. The steelman for flipping now is honest and recorded: if compiled cannot help and cannot hurt routing, the only net effects are the ones that can hurt, so flip it once compiled does something legacy cannot. That condition is exactly what P0 through P3 establish.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:102:- The eventual flip is observable: a per-hub readout shows compiled-serving vs legacy-fallback vs drifted, so a red signal means breakage rather than routine churn.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:104:- The kill-switch stays meaningful: `=0` remains the documented control, and variable-absence keeps its safe legacy meaning until the P4 flip deliberately changes it.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:107:- Four phases of enabling work precede the headline default change. Mitigation: each phase ships standalone value (docs, CI, canary, single-sourced eligibility) rather than being pure overhead.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:113:| Operator overrides to flip now | M | The fallback is genuinely fail-safe today, so an early flip is survivable; but P0 documentation and observability should still land first to satisfy governance and avoid a two-meaning red signal |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:114:| Phased path stalls mid-program | L | Each phase is independently valuable and reversible; stalling leaves the repo in a strictly better documented and observable state than today |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:125:| 1 | **Necessary?** | PASS | The governance gap (undocumented flag) and the silent-drift surface are real today, independent of any future flip |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:127:| 3 | **Sufficient?** | PASS | The phased path is the simplest sequence that makes the flip safe; no step is ornamental |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:129:| 5 | **Open Horizons?** | PASS | Data-driven eligibility (ADR-002) scales to every future skill, so the path does not paint the fleet into a hardcoded corner |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:141:- P0: `ENV-REFERENCE.md` gains the flag entry; the verify harness gains drift-vs-breakage classification and a per-hub serving-status readout.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:142:- P1: a drift-detection CI job plus the enforced rule that editing a hub's routing inputs re-mints its manifest in the same change.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:143:- P2 to P4: a canary env profile, the data-driven eligibility rule (ADR-002), then the staged hub-by-hub default flip.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:145:**How to roll back**: Nothing in this phase changes runtime behavior, so there is nothing to roll back here. Across the program, `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING=0` restores legacy serving fleet-wide, and each per-hub flip retains a byte-identical prior manifest for a byte-exact per-hub revert.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:153:## ADR-002: Single-source compiled eligibility to a valid fresh manifest
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:159:| **Status** | Accepted (design direction; implemented in P3) |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:168:Which hubs are compiled-eligible is hardcoded in two places: `COMPILED_ROUTING_HUBS` in `advisor-recommend.ts:41` and `HUB_CHILD` in `compiled-route.cjs:23`. Two hand-maintained lists drift apart. A newly created skill is compiled-invisible with no defined way to opt in, and `create-skill` today has zero compiled-routing awareness (a repo grep for compiled-routing tokens under the create-skill mode returns nothing).
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:172:- Backward-compat is required: a skill lacking the compiled JSONs or snapshot must route via legacy with no behavior change.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:182:**We chose**: Define compiled eligibility as a single derived predicate: a hub is compiled-eligible if and only if a valid, fresh manifest exists for it (its minted digest matches its live config hash). Both `COMPILED_ROUTING_HUBS` and `HUB_CHILD` derive from that one rule.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:184:**How it works**: Onboarding a skill means minting its manifest; backward-compat means the absence of a manifest yields legacy by construction. `create-skill` (phase 013) mints or scaffolds the manifest step so new hubs are born either compiled-ready or explicitly legacy, never silently half-wired.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:195:| **Data-driven single source (chosen)** | No divergence possible; self-serve onboarding; backward-compat is free by construction | Requires a manifest-freshness read where eligibility is decided | 9/10 |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:196:| One hardcoded list imported by both | Removes duplication cheaply | Still manual; a new skill still needs a code edit to onboard | 6/10 |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:199:**Why this one**: Eligibility should be a property of the artifacts (does a fresh manifest exist), not a fact duplicated in code. That makes onboarding and backward-compat the same mechanism viewed from two sides.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:209:- The two allowlists cannot diverge because neither is authored by hand.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:210:- A new or edited skill has one clear compiled state derived from whether its manifest is fresh.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:213:- Eligibility now reads manifest freshness on the decision path. Mitigation: the freshness check is a hash comparison already computed by the serve-time shim, so it is reused, not added.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:220:| Migration removes the hardcoded sets prematurely | M | Keep the sets as a pinned fallback until P3 parity is proven, then delete in one change |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:231:| 1 | **Necessary?** | PASS | Two hardcoded allowlists exist now and will diverge; new skills have no onboarding path |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:234:| 4 | **Fits Goal?** | PASS | Directly enables a safe global default-on by making eligibility a maintained property, not a code constant |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:235:| 5 | **Open Horizons?** | PASS | Scales to any number of future skills with no code edit per skill |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:247:- P3: a single eligibility predicate keyed on manifest freshness; `COMPILED_ROUTING_HUBS` and `HUB_CHILD` become derived, then removed as hand-authored constants.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:248:- Phase 013: `create-skill` scaffolds the manifest step so onboarding mints eligibility.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:250:**How to roll back**: Retain the hardcoded sets as a pinned fallback through P3; if the derived predicate misbehaves, restore the constants (a one-file revert in each of the two locations).
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:264:| **Status** | Accepted (P0 remediation; promote the resolver) |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:273:The runtime front door `.opencode/bin/compiled-route.cjs` resolves its resolver from a path inside the spec tree: `compiled-route.cjs:16-21` points at `007-unified-refactor-implementation/011-runtime-engine/lib/resolve.cjs`. This repo renumbers and re-nests spec folders constantly (the memory index records repeated hyphen migrations, renumbers, and re-nests). A single such move silently breaks every compiled route to the legacy sentinel, with no observable signal. The repo's own reorganization is a latent drift engine independent of hub-config edits.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:289:**How it works**: `resolve.cjs` moves to a durable runtime path (for example `.opencode/bin/lib/`), and the shim requires it from there. The spec-tree copy becomes the authored source that is built or copied into the runtime location, so a spec renumber no longer moves the file the runtime depends on.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:300:| **Promote resolver to a runtime path (chosen)** | Removes the drift source rather than guarding it; runtime no longer depends on spec-tree layout | A small build or copy step to keep the runtime copy current | 8/10 |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:315:- The runtime dependency graph stops reaching into the spec tree.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:318:- A build or copy step keeps the runtime resolver current. Mitigation: wire it into the same mint/backfill flow that maintains manifests.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:324:| Runtime copy goes stale vs authored source | M | Add a freshness check to the drift-CI (P1) so a stale runtime resolver fails the same gate as a stale manifest |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:338:| 4 | **Fits Goal?** | PASS | A default-on fleet cannot rest on a resolver that a spec move can sever |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:351:- P0: move `resolve.cjs` to a runtime path; update the shim's require; keep the authored source building or copying into place.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:352:- P1: the drift-CI also checks the runtime resolver is current with its authored source.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:364:HVR rules: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/references/hvr-rules.md
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/014-benchmark-alignment/spec.md:2:title: "Feature Specification: Lane C Compiled-Routing Benchmark Alignment"
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/014-benchmark-alignment/spec.md:3:description: "Plan the Lane C harness changes that exercise the compiled router with SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING=1, compare its normalized routing decisions with legacy router replay and the same authored route gold, and classify manifest drift separately from compiled-path breakage without editing the three frozen scorer files."
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/014-benchmark-alignment/spec.md:5:  - "skill benchmark compiled routing alignment"
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/014-benchmark-alignment/spec.md:6:  - "Lane C compiled legacy parity"
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/014-benchmark-alignment/spec.md:7:  - "compiled routing drift benchmark"
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/014-benchmark-alignment/spec.md:21:# Lane C Compiled-Routing Benchmark Alignment
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/014-benchmark-alignment/spec.md:25:Lane C currently benchmarks deterministic routing through `router-replay.cjs`, joins the observed result to authored route gold, and scores it through `score-skill-benchmark.cjs`. The orchestrator never turns on `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING`, never invokes the compiled front door, and never compares the compiled decision with the legacy replay. A hub can therefore pass the benchmark while the path intended to serve under the compiled flag is stale, falling back, or broken.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/014-benchmark-alignment/spec.md:27:This phase plans a harness around the frozen scorer. For each eligible hub and authored route-gold scenario, Lane C will preserve the existing legacy observation, invoke the public compiled front door in a child process with the flag set to `1`, normalize both outputs to the same routing projection, assert each against the same route gold, and require compiled-versus-legacy routing equality. Drift and no-manifest states use the classifications owned by `../012-default-on-decision/`; this packet references those contracts and does not restate them.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/014-benchmark-alignment/spec.md:37:| **Priority** | P0 |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/014-benchmark-alignment/spec.md:40:| **Branch** | `skilled/v4.0.0.0` |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/014-benchmark-alignment/spec.md:41:| **Lane** | Lane C (`skill-benchmark`) |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/014-benchmark-alignment/spec.md:42:| **Blast radius** | Deterministic benchmark harness, reporting, fixtures, and tests; no routing policy or scorer semantics change |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/014-benchmark-alignment/spec.md:52:`run-skill-benchmark.cjs` resolves a skill root, runs structural gates, loads scenarios, dispatches router-mode cases, calls `scoreScenario()`/`evaluateRouteGold()`, aggregates, and writes the JSON/Markdown reports. In deterministic Mode A, `executor-dispatch.cjs` selects `router-replay.cjs`. Hub route-gold is enforced by default, but the observed route is still the legacy replay only.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/014-benchmark-alignment/spec.md:54:The existing seam is suitable for an additive parity lane: `router-replay.cjs` returns legacy intents/resources and hub telemetry; `.opencode/bin/compiled-route.cjs` returns the flag-gated compiled decision or a legacy sentinel; `score-skill-benchmark.cjs` already exports the route-gold evaluator. The missing piece is normalization and comparison around those unchanged modules.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/014-benchmark-alignment/spec.md:58:Lane C validates authored routing but not the path that will serve when compiled routing is enabled. It cannot prove that the flag-on front door actually returns a compiled decision, that the decision matches the legacy route, or that stale-manifest fallback is distinguishable from a broken compiled path. Adding compiled logic inside the scorer would corrupt the pinned baseline and mix routing observation with scoring policy.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/014-benchmark-alignment/spec.md:62:Add a deterministic compiled-routing parity harness, integrate its structured result into Lane C reporting and process gates, and cover fresh, drifted, missing, and broken fixture states. The three frozen scorer files remain byte-identical and are consumed read-only.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/014-benchmark-alignment/spec.md:72:- A new harness module beside the Lane C orchestrator that owns compiled invocation, result normalization, parity comparison, status classification, and scorer-digest pinning.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/014-benchmark-alignment/spec.md:73:- Child-process invocation of `.opencode/bin/compiled-route.cjs` with `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING=1` for eligible hubs so the real public flag-gated path is exercised.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/014-benchmark-alignment/spec.md:74:- Legacy observation through the existing frozen `router-replay.cjs`.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/014-benchmark-alignment/spec.md:75:- Route-gold checks for both normalized observations through the existing frozen `evaluateRouteGold()` export.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/014-benchmark-alignment/spec.md:77:- A default-on parity gate for hubs whose shared eligibility predicate reports a valid fresh manifest; no-manifest hubs are recorded as legacy by construction rather than treated as a compiled failure.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/014-benchmark-alignment/spec.md:83:- Editing the frozen files `router-replay.cjs`, `score-skill-benchmark.cjs`, or `load-playbook-scenarios.cjs`.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/014-benchmark-alignment/spec.md:84:- Changing D1-D5 weights, route-gold semantics, scenario loading, authored gold, routing decisions, or manifest contents.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/014-benchmark-alignment/spec.md:85:- Using real models or network calls; this alignment is deterministic Mode A coverage.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/014-benchmark-alignment/spec.md:86:- Defining fallback, eligibility, or observability semantics; those remain authoritative in the decision packet.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/014-benchmark-alignment/spec.md:87:- Generating or re-minting production manifests during a benchmark run. Drift is reported, never repaired automatically.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/014-benchmark-alignment/spec.md:93:1. `.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/router-replay.cjs`
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/014-benchmark-alignment/spec.md:94:2. `.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/score-skill-benchmark.cjs`
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/014-benchmark-alignment/spec.md:95:3. `.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/load-playbook-scenarios.cjs`
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/014-benchmark-alignment/spec.md:101:1. Obtain the legacy observation from `routeSkillResources()`.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/014-benchmark-alignment/spec.md:105:5. Call the frozen route-gold evaluator for both projected observations.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/014-benchmark-alignment/spec.md:113:| `.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/compiled-routing-parity.cjs` | Create | Own compiled invocation, normalization, status classification, parity, and frozen-file hashes |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/014-benchmark-alignment/spec.md:114:| `.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/run-skill-benchmark.cjs` | Modify | Run the parity lane for eligible hub scenarios, gate the verdict, and preserve current scoring |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/014-benchmark-alignment/spec.md:115:| `.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/build-report.cjs` | Modify | Render the `compiledRouting` block from report JSON |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/014-benchmark-alignment/spec.md:116:| `.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/README.md` | Modify | Document the parity gate, status meanings by reference, and CLI behavior |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/014-benchmark-alignment/spec.md:117:| `.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/tests/compiled-routing-parity.vitest.ts` | Create | Cover fresh parity, divergence, drift, no-manifest, breakage, and env isolation |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/014-benchmark-alignment/spec.md:118:| `.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/tests/fixtures/compiled-routing/` | Create | Deterministic copied/minimal fixture states around the harness |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/014-benchmark-alignment/spec.md:128:### P0 - Blockers (MUST complete)
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/014-benchmark-alignment/spec.md:133:| REQ-002 | Exercise the real compiled-serving path with the flag on. | Eligible hub scenarios invoke `.opencode/bin/compiled-route.cjs` in a child process with `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING=1`; the report records `flagForcedOn: true` and the front-door outcome. |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/014-benchmark-alignment/spec.md:134:| REQ-003 | Require route-gold success and routing equality for compiled and legacy observations. | Both projected observations pass the same authored route gold and their normalized routing projections compare equal; a mismatch names scenario, legacy projection, compiled projection, and first differing field. |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/014-benchmark-alignment/spec.md:135:| REQ-004 | Distinguish manifest drift, legacy-by-construction, and compiled breakage. | Status comes from the shared decision-contract probe: no manifest records legacy-only; stale manifest records drift and re-mint-required; fresh manifest plus resolver/front-door failure records breakage. |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/014-benchmark-alignment/spec.md:136:| REQ-005 | Integrate parity as a Lane C gate without changing D1-D5. | `report.compiledRouting` contains mode, eligible rows, parity counts, drift rows, breakages, and frozen hashes; routing divergence or breakage produces a distinct blocked verdict and non-zero exit, while drift remains visibly classified according to the authoritative contract. |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/014-benchmark-alignment/spec.md:137:| REQ-006 | Prevent environment and filesystem mutation. | Each compiled call receives a child-only env; parent `process.env` is unchanged; benchmark runs never mint, modify, or delete a manifest or routing input. |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/014-benchmark-alignment/spec.md:139:### P1 - Required (complete OR user-approved deferral)
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/014-benchmark-alignment/spec.md:143:| REQ-007 | Cover the full state matrix with deterministic fixtures. | Vitest covers fresh parity, forced divergence, stale manifest, missing manifest, malformed/fresh breakage, explicit flag isolation, and frozen-file hash drift detection. |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/014-benchmark-alignment/spec.md:144:| REQ-008 | Keep JSON, Markdown, CLI, and README semantics synchronized. | Report JSON is authoritative; Markdown renders from it; CLI usage describes the new gate; documentation references rather than duplicates the decision contracts. |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/014-benchmark-alignment/spec.md:152:- **SC-001**: Every eligible route-gold row exercises the public flag-on compiled front door.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/014-benchmark-alignment/spec.md:153:- **SC-002**: Compiled and legacy observations each satisfy the same authored route gold and compare equal on routing fields.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/014-benchmark-alignment/spec.md:155:- **SC-004**: Drift, missing-manifest legacy, and fresh-manifest breakage are reported as different states using the authoritative shared classifier.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/014-benchmark-alignment/spec.md:156:- **SC-005**: D1-D5 scores for an unchanged legacy run remain identical before and after the alignment.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/014-benchmark-alignment/spec.md:157:- **SC-006**: The three frozen file hashes are identical before and after implementation and every benchmark run.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/014-benchmark-alignment/spec.md:163:## 6. RISKS & DEPENDENCIES
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/014-benchmark-alignment/spec.md:167:| Dependency | P0 stable compiled front door and status probe | Current front door depends on a spec-tree resolver path and sentinel alone lacks cause | Consume the stable P0 interface; keep the CLI path public and cause classification shared |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/014-benchmark-alignment/spec.md:168:| Dependency | P3 eligibility predicate and manifest discovery | Harness cannot know whether to expect compiled serving without it | Gate parity only through the shared predicate; no local hub list |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/014-benchmark-alignment/spec.md:170:| Risk | Harness accidentally changes scorer meaning | Existing aggregate scores drift | Add before/after legacy report fixture; keep new verdict logic in the orchestrator |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/014-benchmark-alignment/spec.md:171:| Risk | Test mutates production manifest to simulate drift | Benchmark fixture leaks into live state | Copy inputs into temp fixtures or inject path adapters; never edit live manifests |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/014-benchmark-alignment/spec.md:172:| Risk | Child env leaks into the parent test process | Later tests observe flag-on behavior | Pass a cloned env to spawn and assert parent env before/after |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/014-benchmark-alignment/spec.md:183:- **NFR-D01**: Router-mode parity runs offline and returns identical results for identical skill, manifest, and scenario bytes.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/014-benchmark-alignment/spec.md:188:- **NFR-I01**: The flag is scoped to the compiled child process only.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/014-benchmark-alignment/spec.md:193:- **NFR-C01**: Non-hub and no-manifest runs keep their existing D1-D5 results and gain only an explicit legacy/not-applicable parity status.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/014-benchmark-alignment/spec.md:206:- Legacy router unparseable: retain the current structural failure; do not run parity against an undefined baseline.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/014-benchmark-alignment/spec.md:208:### Eligibility and Serving
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/014-benchmark-alignment/spec.md:210:- No manifest: record legacy-by-construction and skip the compiled parity expectation.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/014-benchmark-alignment/spec.md:211:- Stale manifest: record drift/re-mint-required; do not report generic compiled breakage.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/014-benchmark-alignment/spec.md:212:- Valid fresh manifest but front door returns sentinel or invalid JSON: report broken compiled path.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/014-benchmark-alignment/spec.md:213:- Flag already set in parent process: child still receives an explicit `1`, and the parent value is unchanged after the call.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/014-benchmark-alignment/spec.md:217:- Scenario without route gold: omit from the hard parity denominator or record diagnostic-only status; never fabricate gold.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/014-benchmark-alignment/spec.md:219:- Compiled differs only in hash or generation: routing parity passes because metadata is outside the projection.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/014-benchmark-alignment/spec.md:230:| Risk | 14/25 | CI gate around a live front door, bounded by deterministic child processes and frozen scorer |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/014-benchmark-alignment/spec.md:240:- Should a drifted live hub make Lane C exit non-zero directly, or should Lane C report the degraded state while the separate P1 drift-CI job owns the failing process signal? The report must distinguish drift from breakage either way.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/014-benchmark-alignment/spec.md:241:- What stable machine-readable P0 status-probe interface will return the cause behind a legacy sentinel?
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/014-benchmark-alignment/spec.md:242:- Should the parity gate default to `auto` for valid-fresh hubs and `off/not-applicable` elsewhere, or use an explicit `--compiled-routing-parity on|off|auto` flag mirroring route-gold? The recommendation is `auto` with a recorded resolved mode.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/014-benchmark-alignment/spec.md:249:- **Fallback, eligibility, drift, and observability authority**: `../012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md`
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/014-benchmark-alignment/spec.md:250:- **Default-on program**: `../012-default-on-decision/spec.md`
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/014-benchmark-alignment/spec.md:255:- **Current Lane C architecture**: `.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/README.md`
