.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/014-benchmark-alignment/implementation-summary.md:6:  - "benchmark parity current status"
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/014-benchmark-alignment/implementation-summary.md:10:# Implementation Summary: Lane C Compiled-Routing Benchmark Alignment
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/014-benchmark-alignment/implementation-summary.md:27:| **Frozen scorer state** | Pinned and untouched by this documentation phase |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/014-benchmark-alignment/implementation-summary.md:36:Lane C will gain a deterministic parity module around the existing scorer. For eligible route-gold scenarios it will preserve the legacy replay, invoke the real public compiled front door with a child-only flag-on environment, normalize both routing results, run the same gold evaluator twice, and require mutual routing equality.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/014-benchmark-alignment/implementation-summary.md:42:| Parity harness | `compiled-routing-parity.cjs` | Invocation, normalization, status, equality, and digest checks |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/014-benchmark-alignment/implementation-summary.md:43:| Orchestration | `run-skill-benchmark.cjs` | Eligible-row execution and distinct gate |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/014-benchmark-alignment/implementation-summary.md:48:No Lane C runtime file, fixture, report renderer, manifest, routing input, or frozen scorer file was modified by this planning phase.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/014-benchmark-alignment/implementation-summary.md:56:Implementation waits for the stable P0 front-door/status interface and P3 eligibility/discovery interface. After baseline reports and hashes are captured, the new module lands first, then orchestrator/report integration, then the isolated state matrix and non-regression suite. The frozen modules are imported and hashed only.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/014-benchmark-alignment/implementation-summary.md:66:| Keep compiled alignment outside the scorer | Preserves the pinned D1-D5 and route-gold baseline while adding a new observation path. |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/014-benchmark-alignment/implementation-summary.md:67:| Exercise the public front door in a child process | Tests the real flag and serving gates and prevents parent environment leakage. |
