.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/013-create-skill-alignment/spec.md:2:title: "Feature Specification: create-skill Compiled-Routing Alignment"
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/013-create-skill-alignment/spec.md:3:description: "Plan the create-skill onboarding changes that make newly generated parent hubs match v4 compiled-routing reality: every generated hub receives the same additive compiled-routing directive as the seven existing hubs, while an explicit onboarding mode either mints and verifies a fresh activation manifest or deliberately emits no manifest and remains legacy by construction."
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/013-create-skill-alignment/spec.md:5:  - "create-skill compiled routing alignment"
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/013-create-skill-alignment/spec.md:7:  - "create-skill activation manifest step"
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/013-create-skill-alignment/spec.md:21:# create-skill Compiled-Routing Alignment
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/013-create-skill-alignment/spec.md:25:`sk-doc:create-skill` can generate a parent hub, its registry/router metadata, and its first workflow packet, but it currently emits no compiled-routing directive, no activation-manifest step, and no compiled-readiness verification. A repository search beneath `.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-skill/` returns zero compiled-routing tokens. The generated hub therefore reflects the pre-v4 routing model even though the seven established hubs now carry the additive, flag-gated directive.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/013-create-skill-alignment/spec.md:27:This phase plans the onboarding-side implementation of the eligibility decision owned by `../012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md`. A generated parent hub must be born in one of two explicit states: **compiled-ready**, where create-skill mints and verifies the canonical fresh manifest, or **legacy**, where no manifest is emitted and the hub follows the existing routing path by construction. This packet references the authoritative fallback and eligibility contract; it does not redefine it.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/013-create-skill-alignment/spec.md:37:| **Priority** | P0 |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/013-create-skill-alignment/spec.md:40:| **Branch** | `skilled/v4.0.0.0` |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/013-create-skill-alignment/spec.md:41:| **Consumed decision** | `../012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md` (eligibility and fallback authority) |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/013-create-skill-alignment/spec.md:42:| **Blast radius** | Generator and templates only during implementation; existing skills remain unchanged unless regenerated explicitly |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/013-create-skill-alignment/spec.md:52:The active parent-hub generator is `scripts/init_skill.py::init_parent_skill()`. It reads `assets/parent-skill/scaffold/hub-skill-scaffold.md`, creates `SKILL.md`, `README.md`, `mode-registry.json`, `hub-router.json`, `graph-metadata.json`, `description.json`, hub support directories, and one primary packet. Its CLI exposes only `--kind standalone|parent`. The generated hub `SKILL.md` routes through the registry and prose router only.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/013-create-skill-alignment/spec.md:54:The copy-from parent template, `assets/parent-skill/parent-skill-hub-template.md`, likewise contains no compiled directive. The broader create-skill workflow documents parent-hub metadata and validation, but never asks whether the new hub should mint compiled eligibility. Existing tests in `.opencode/skills/sk-doc/scripts/tests/test_create_skill_contract.py` verify the emitted paths and naming, not compiled state.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/013-create-skill-alignment/spec.md:58:New parent hubs cannot express a deliberate compiled state. They neither receive the directive used by the current seven hubs nor have an onboarding action that can mint the manifest on which compiled eligibility depends. Adding only the directive would leave a hub permanently falling back; adding only a manifest would leave its `SKILL.md` unaware of the compiled front door. The two surfaces must be generated together, with legacy remaining the backward-compatible state when no manifest is requested.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/013-create-skill-alignment/spec.md:62:Align create-skill with the v4 router model by adding the exact directive block, an explicit compiled-readiness selection, a canonical manifest-mint step, and contract tests that prove both generated states. The current implementation files remain unchanged in this documentation phase.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/013-create-skill-alignment/spec.md:72:- Parent-hub generation through `init_skill.py --kind parent`; standalone-skill scaffolding remains unchanged.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/013-create-skill-alignment/spec.md:73:- A new `--compiled-routing legacy|ready` option. Existing CLI calls default to `legacy` for backward compatibility; the higher-level create-skill workflow must ask authors to choose explicitly.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/013-create-skill-alignment/spec.md:75:- A post-scaffold manifest step for `ready`: call the canonical minter supplied by the P3 eligibility implementation, then verify the returned manifest is valid and fresh before reporting compiled-ready.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/013-create-skill-alignment/spec.md:76:- The `legacy` state: do not mint a manifest; report the generated hub as legacy by construction.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/013-create-skill-alignment/spec.md:77:- Create-skill workflow, README/reference, validator, and contract-test updates needed to keep the generated output and documentation synchronized.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/013-create-skill-alignment/spec.md:78:- Failure behavior that never reports compiled-ready after a missing, stale, malformed, or failed manifest mint.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/013-create-skill-alignment/spec.md:83:- Implementing the P3 runtime discovery and canonical manifest store; create-skill consumes those interfaces after they exist.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/013-create-skill-alignment/spec.md:84:- Changing the compiled router's decisions, the advisor recommendation, environment defaults, existing hub manifests, or existing hub directives.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/013-create-skill-alignment/spec.md:85:- Editing `router-replay.cjs`, `score-skill-benchmark.cjs`, or `load-playbook-scenarios.cjs`.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/013-create-skill-alignment/spec.md:86:- Retrofitting existing skills automatically; migration of existing hubs requires a separate explicit operation.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/013-create-skill-alignment/spec.md:93:> **Compiled routing (opt-in, flag-gated, additive).** When `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING=1`, resolve the mode via the compiled router contract first:
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/013-create-skill-alignment/spec.md:97:> Follow the returned decision — `route` (use its `targets`), `clarify`/`defer` (disambiguate), `reject` (refuse). On a `{"servingAuthority":"legacy"}` sentinel or any error, use the routing below. The front door self-gates on serving authority, and the flag is **off by default**, so this is inert until compiled routing is activated for `{{HUB_NAME}}`.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/013-create-skill-alignment/spec.md:100:`init_skill.py` resolves both `{{HUB_NAME}}` occurrences to the generated hub name. A legacy scaffold still receives this additive directive; the missing manifest causes the authoritative fallback path, making legacy status explicit and safe rather than leaving a different template shape.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/013-create-skill-alignment/spec.md:106:| `.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-skill/scripts/init_skill.py` | Modify | Add the parent-only compiled state option, render the directive, invoke the canonical minter for `ready`, and report verified state |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/013-create-skill-alignment/spec.md:107:| `.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-skill/assets/parent-skill/scaffold/hub-skill-scaffold.md` | Modify | Add the generated directive block used by the active initializer |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/013-create-skill-alignment/spec.md:108:| `.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-skill/assets/parent-skill/parent-skill-hub-template.md` | Modify | Add the matching block to the copy-from canonical template |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/013-create-skill-alignment/spec.md:109:| `.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-skill/SKILL.md` | Modify | Add the explicit onboarding decision and ordered manifest step |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/013-create-skill-alignment/spec.md:110:| `.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-skill/README.md` | Modify | Document generated compiled states and examples |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/013-create-skill-alignment/spec.md:111:| `.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-skill/references/parent-skill/parent-skills-nested-packets.md` | Modify | Document the parent-hub readiness choice without duplicating the eligibility contract |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/013-create-skill-alignment/spec.md:112:| `.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-skill/scripts/validate_skill_package.py` | Modify if required by the chosen P3 API | Report directive/manifest consistency and freshness through the shared predicate |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/013-create-skill-alignment/spec.md:113:| `.opencode/skills/sk-doc/scripts/tests/test_create_skill_contract.py` | Modify | Add legacy, compiled-ready, directive-rendering, and mint-failure regression cases |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/013-create-skill-alignment/spec.md:115:> No file in this table is modified by this planning-only phase.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/013-create-skill-alignment/spec.md:123:### P0 - Blockers (MUST complete)
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/013-create-skill-alignment/spec.md:127:| REQ-001 | Consume the eligibility and fallback decision without redefining it. | create-skill calls the shared P3 minter/freshness interface and links to the decision packet; no local allowlist, freshness algorithm, or alternate fallback rule is introduced. |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/013-create-skill-alignment/spec.md:129:| REQ-003 | Expose two deliberate generated states. | `--compiled-routing legacy|ready` is parent-only; existing CLI calls default to `legacy`; the higher-level workflow asks for a choice; output states either `legacy (no manifest)` or `compiled-ready (fresh manifest verified)`. |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/013-create-skill-alignment/spec.md:130:| REQ-004 | Mint real eligibility for compiled-ready hubs. | `ready` invokes the canonical minter after final router inputs exist, receives the canonical manifest location, and validates freshness through the shared predicate before success output. No synthetic digest or hand-authored manifest is accepted. |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/013-create-skill-alignment/spec.md:131:| REQ-005 | Fail closed without a half-wired success state. | Missing minter, mint error, malformed manifest, or stale digest produces a non-zero result and never prints compiled-ready. The output names the retained legacy fallback or diagnostic path explicitly. |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/013-create-skill-alignment/spec.md:132:| REQ-006 | Preserve legacy compatibility. | `legacy` emits no manifest, the generated directive falls through safely, existing `--kind parent` calls remain valid, and standalone scaffolding is byte-equivalent except for unrelated timestamp fields. |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/013-create-skill-alignment/spec.md:134:### P1 - Required (complete OR user-approved deferral)
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/013-create-skill-alignment/spec.md:138:| REQ-007 | Add contract tests and package validation for both states. | Tests cover directive substitution, legacy no-manifest output, ready fresh-manifest output through a test minter, stale/malformed rejection, unknown option rejection, and unchanged standalone behavior. |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/013-create-skill-alignment/spec.md:139:| REQ-008 | Keep authoring documentation synchronized. | `SKILL.md`, README, parent reference, active scaffold, and canonical template describe the same option names, ordering, and status language. |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/013-create-skill-alignment/spec.md:148:- **SC-002**: `legacy` generation emits no manifest and is reported as legacy by construction.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/013-create-skill-alignment/spec.md:149:- **SC-003**: `ready` generation is reported as compiled-ready only after the canonical manifest exists and the shared predicate confirms freshness.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/013-create-skill-alignment/spec.md:158:## 6. RISKS & DEPENDENCIES
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/013-create-skill-alignment/spec.md:162:| Dependency | P3 canonical minter, manifest store, and freshness predicate | `ready` cannot be truthful without them | Gate implementation on the stable P3 interface; never emulate it inside create-skill |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/013-create-skill-alignment/spec.md:163:| Dependency | Data-driven runtime hub discovery | A fresh manifest alone cannot route a hub if the runtime still uses a fixed hub map | Require P3 runtime discovery before advertising ready mode |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/013-create-skill-alignment/spec.md:165:| Risk | Backward-compatible default hides an author choice | Existing scripts need a default, but agent workflows should not silently choose | CLI defaults to legacy; create-skill workflow asks explicitly and reports the selected state |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/013-create-skill-alignment/spec.md:166:| Risk | Partial scaffold remains after a mint failure | Files may exist although the command exits non-zero | Print a clear diagnostic and legacy state; do not write a success marker or synthetic manifest |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/013-create-skill-alignment/spec.md:167:| Risk | P4 later changes directive semantics | The generated block could become stale | Treat the active scaffold and seven hub directives as one lockstep surface in P4 |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/013-create-skill-alignment/spec.md:177:- **NFR-D01**: Given the same hub inputs and P3 minter version, manifest minting and readiness classification are deterministic.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/013-create-skill-alignment/spec.md:187:- **NFR-A01**: create-skill may request and verify eligibility but cannot define it; the shared predicate remains authoritative.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/013-create-skill-alignment/spec.md:201:### Manifest Outcomes
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/013-create-skill-alignment/spec.md:205:- Manifest exists but live inputs changed before verification: stale result; report re-mint required.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/013-create-skill-alignment/spec.md:206:- Legacy selection with a pre-existing manifest at the target identity: halt and require an explicit reconciliation decision rather than silently deleting or reusing it.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/013-create-skill-alignment/spec.md:222:| Risk | 12/25 | Backward-compatible default and fail-safe fallback bound runtime risk |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/013-create-skill-alignment/spec.md:223:| Research | 8/20 | Depends on the stable P3 minter and manifest-location interface |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/013-create-skill-alignment/spec.md:232:- What exact callable/CLI name and return schema will P3 expose for canonical manifest minting and freshness verification?
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/013-create-skill-alignment/spec.md:233:- Will the P3 canonical manifest live beside each hub, in a central runtime store, or behind an abstract resolver? create-skill must consume the interface rather than bind to the current phase-local path.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/013-create-skill-alignment/spec.md:241:- **Eligibility and fallback authority**: `../012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md`
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/013-create-skill-alignment/spec.md:242:- **Default-on program**: `../012-default-on-decision/spec.md`
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/013-create-skill-alignment/spec.md:247:- **Current create-skill workflow**: `.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-skill/SKILL.md`
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/013-create-skill-alignment/spec.md:248:- **Current parent initializer**: `.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-skill/scripts/init_skill.py`
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/013-create-skill-alignment/implementation-summary.md:2:title: "Implementation Summary: create-skill Compiled-Routing Alignment"
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/013-create-skill-alignment/implementation-summary.md:3:description: "Planned-state record for aligning create-skill's parent-hub generator with compiled-routing directives and manifest-based onboarding. No generator or runtime implementation is present yet."
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/013-create-skill-alignment/implementation-summary.md:5:  - "create-skill compiled routing planned summary"
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/013-create-skill-alignment/implementation-summary.md:10:# Implementation Summary: create-skill Compiled-Routing Alignment
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/013-create-skill-alignment/implementation-summary.md:26:| **Current create-skill awareness** | Zero compiled-routing tokens beneath the packet |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/013-create-skill-alignment/implementation-summary.md:35:The parent-hub generator will gain the same additive compiled-routing directive used by the seven established hubs and an explicit onboarding state. Legacy generation will omit the canonical manifest and remain on the fallback path. Ready generation will invoke the shared minter and report compiled-ready only after the shared predicate confirms freshness.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/013-create-skill-alignment/implementation-summary.md:41:| Generator | `create-skill/scripts/init_skill.py` | Parse parent state, render hub name, mint and verify ready manifests |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/013-create-skill-alignment/implementation-summary.md:43:| Workflow | create-skill `SKILL.md`, README, and parent reference | Ask the state explicitly and document the ordered manifest step |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/013-create-skill-alignment/implementation-summary.md:44:| Validation | `validate_skill_package.py` and create-skill contract tests | Prove both states and fail-closed outcomes |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/013-create-skill-alignment/implementation-summary.md:46:No create-skill, runtime, manifest, or scorer file was modified by this planning phase.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/013-create-skill-alignment/implementation-summary.md:54:Implementation waits for the P3 minter, freshness predicate, canonical manifest location, and data-driven runtime discovery. After those interfaces stabilize, the two templates move together, the initializer gains the state adapter, and the existing create-skill contract suite expands to cover legacy, ready, and failure outcomes before any adoption claim.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/013-create-skill-alignment/implementation-summary.md:64:| Add the directive to every generated parent hub | Legacy and ready hubs should share one durable SKILL.md shape; eligibility is determined by the manifest state. |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/013-create-skill-alignment/implementation-summary.md:65:| Default existing CLI calls to legacy | Preserves automation compatibility and the safe no-manifest state. |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/013-create-skill-alignment/implementation-summary.md:66:| Require the authoring workflow to ask explicitly | Human/agent-created hubs should not hide the onboarding decision behind a compatibility default. |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/013-create-skill-alignment/implementation-summary.md:67:| Delegate minting and freshness to P3 interfaces | Prevents a second eligibility algorithm or hardcoded hub map inside create-skill. |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/013-create-skill-alignment/implementation-summary.md:80:| Legacy no-manifest test | Planned |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/013-create-skill-alignment/implementation-summary.md:81:| Ready fresh-manifest test | Planned |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/013-create-skill-alignment/implementation-summary.md:84:| Strict skill-package and spec-folder validation | Planned spec command: `bash .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/spec/validate.sh .opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/013-create-skill-alignment --strict` |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/013-create-skill-alignment/implementation-summary.md:92:1. **Ready mode depends on P3 interfaces that do not exist yet.** This packet cannot truthfully select a manifest location or eligibility result before those interfaces stabilize.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/013-create-skill-alignment/implementation-summary.md:93:2. **Current runtime discovery is limited to established hubs.** A new hub cannot become operationally compiled-ready until P3 removes that fixed discovery boundary.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/013-create-skill-alignment/implementation-summary.md:94:3. **Existing hubs are not migrated by this phase.** The generator affects new explicit runs only.
