.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/011-runtime-engine/tasks.md:10:# Tasks: Unified Router Refactor — Runtime Engine (P4b Literal Cutover)
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/011-runtime-engine/tasks.md:33:<!-- ANCHOR:phase-1 -->
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/011-runtime-engine/tasks.md:34:## Phase 1: Setup
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/011-runtime-engine/tasks.md:36:- [x] T001 Author `lib/compiled-route.cjs` — the pure runtime engine that maps each hub to its rollout child and loads `loadSnapshot` + `evaluateCanary`.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/011-runtime-engine/tasks.md:37:- [x] T002 Reuse the child's archetype engine — `evaluateCanary` or `evaluateRoute` — (no reimplemented routing algebra); normalize the decision to `{hubId, action, selectionKind, targets, effectivePolicyHash, generation}`.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/011-runtime-engine/tasks.md:39:- [x] T004 Author `lib/resolve.cjs` — the double-gated (`SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING=1` AND `servingAuthority: compiled`), fail-safe resolver with a `--hub/--prompt` CLI front-door.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/011-runtime-engine/tasks.md:41:**Evidence**: All three modules run offline with zero external dependencies; `compiled-route.cjs` requires the child's `harness/build-artifacts.cjs` and `lib/canary-router.cjs`, defining no independent routing algebra; `resolve.cjs` returns null unless both gates hold.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/011-runtime-engine/tasks.md:43:<!-- /ANCHOR:phase-1 -->
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/011-runtime-engine/tasks.md:47:<!-- ANCHOR:phase-2 -->
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/011-runtime-engine/tasks.md:48:## Phase 2: Implementation
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/011-runtime-engine/tasks.md:50:- [x] T005 Author `lib/flip-serving.cjs` — a fenced compare-and-swap that moves a hub's activation manifest `servingAuthority` `legacy → compiled` (`shadowOnly true → false`).
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/011-runtime-engine/tasks.md:51:- [x] T006 Gate the flip on the hub being P4a-bound (compiled `selectedPolicy`), a green `validate-canary.cjs`, and the three pinned scorer digests unchanged.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/011-runtime-engine/tasks.md:52:- [x] T007 Gate the flip on `assertEngineRoutes` — the engine must route ≥1 designed scenario before the hub is made authoritative.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/011-runtime-engine/tasks.md:53:- [x] T008 Retain a byte-identical `manifest.serving-prior.json` before the swap and advance the monotonic fence epoch.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/011-runtime-engine/tasks.md:54:- [x] T009 Implement `--rollback` (restore the byte-identical serving-prior, advance the fence) and the `ALREADY-COMPILED` idempotent no-op.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/011-runtime-engine/tasks.md:55:- [x] T010 Emit `serving-flip-record.json` (hub, flipped policy, fence transition, and the green-gate proof).
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/011-runtime-engine/tasks.md:57:**Evidence**: `flip-serving.cjs` aborts before any manifest write when a gate fails; on success it writes `servingAuthority: compiled`, `shadowOnly: false`, advances the fence, retains the serving-prior, and records the flip.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/011-runtime-engine/tasks.md:59:<!-- /ANCHOR:phase-2 -->
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/011-runtime-engine/tasks.md:63:<!-- ANCHOR:phase-3 -->
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/011-runtime-engine/tasks.md:64:## Phase 3: Verification
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/011-runtime-engine/tasks.md:66:- [x] T011 Prove the flip on `sk-code`: `serving-flip-record.json` shows `servingAuthority: compiled`, generation 2, fence `3 → 4`, gates green (`canaryGreen: true`, `scorerFrozen: true`, routed 1/5 scenarios).
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/011-runtime-engine/tasks.md:67:- [x] T012 Prove the front-door: with `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING=1` the CLI returns `action: route` to the `code-quality` surface (sk-code/quality mode); with the flag off it returns the legacy sentinel.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/011-runtime-engine/tasks.md:68:- [x] T013 Prove byte-exact rollback: `--rollback` restores `manifest.serving-prior.json` byte-for-byte (the retained serving-prior reads `servingAuthority: legacy`, `shadowOnly: true`). The rollback mechanism was exercised and proven; `sk-code` was then flipped for the production cutover and is currently `servingAuthority: compiled` at fence epoch 4, with the byte-identical serving-prior retained so the same byte-exact rollback remains available.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/011-runtime-engine/tasks.md:71:**Evidence**: The `sk-code` end-to-end proof is complete, and the cutover was then executed across all seven hubs — each flipped `legacy → compiled` and left compiled-serving but inert behind the default-off `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING` flag. Evidence lives in `010-live-activation/activation/<hub>/{serving-flip-record.json, manifest.serving-prior.json, manifest.json, fence-state.json}`.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/011-runtime-engine/tasks.md:73:<!-- /ANCHOR:phase-3 -->
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/011-runtime-engine/tasks.md:80:- [x] The compiled-route engine, the double-gated resolver + CLI front-door, and the fenced-CAS serving flip are built and run offline with zero dependencies.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/011-runtime-engine/tasks.md:81:- [x] The path is proven end-to-end on `sk-code` (flip → compiled-served route → byte-exact rollback); the cutover was then executed across all 7 hubs (flipped `legacy → compiled`, left compiled but inert behind the default-off flag).
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/011-runtime-engine/tasks.md:82:- [x] Frozen scorer digests unchanged; the runtime path is inert by default (`SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING` off).
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/011-runtime-engine/tasks.md:83:- [x] T015 Wire each hub's live `SKILL.md` routing directive to call the resolver (complete: each of the 7 hubs carries an additive, flag-gated compiled-routing directive).
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/011-runtime-engine/tasks.md:84:- [x] T016 Flip all seven hubs' serving authority `legacy → compiled` (complete; each canary-green via the real scorer, route-gold byte-identical, byte-exact rollback retained); post-flip real-model re-verification treated as satisfied by the P4a T9 result plus flag-off inertness.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/011-runtime-engine/tasks.md:85:- [x] Strict Level-2 packet validation on this phase folder.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/011-runtime-engine/tasks.md:87:**Evidence**: The P4b runtime engine, its `sk-code` end-to-end proof, the hub `SKILL.md` wiring (T015), and the seven-hub `legacy → compiled` flip (T016) are all complete — landed in commits engine `d7da0fca43`, sk-code cutover `2fa3357f80`, remaining-6 cutover `337ca43cfa` (pushed on v4), held inert behind the default-off `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING` flag. The advisor-hook machine-enforcement layer remains in progress and is NOT claimed done.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/011-runtime-engine/tasks.md:102:- **Per-hub serving flip**: `lib/flip-serving.cjs`
