.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/011-runtime-engine/plan.md:2:title: "Implementation Plan: Unified Router Refactor — Runtime Engine (P4b Literal Cutover)"
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/011-runtime-engine/plan.md:3:description: "How the archetype-adaptive compiled-route engine reuses each child's proven engine (evaluateCanary or evaluateRoute), how the double-gated resolver keeps the cutover inert by default, and how the fenced-CAS flip moved all seven hubs legacy→compiled with a byte-exact rollback."
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/011-runtime-engine/plan.md:7:  - "P4b cutover plan"
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/011-runtime-engine/plan.md:11:# Implementation Plan: Unified Router Refactor — Runtime Engine (P4b Literal Cutover)
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/011-runtime-engine/plan.md:18:- Match phases to the stated scope; remove setup theater that does not change the outcome.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/011-runtime-engine/plan.md:20:- Over-planning, missing rollback, and treating assumptions as dependencies.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/011-runtime-engine/plan.md:32:| **Language/Stack** | Zero-dependency CommonJS (Node built-ins only) |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/011-runtime-engine/plan.md:33:| **Routing engine** | Archetype-adaptive: reuses each rollout child's `loadSnapshot` and its engine — `evaluateCanary` (surfaceBundle canary-router) or `evaluateRoute` (plain router) — the same closed decision algebra the shadow canary validates |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/011-runtime-engine/plan.md:34:| **Serving gate** | Double gate: runtime flag `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING=1` AND manifest `servingAuthority: compiled`; default off = inert |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/011-runtime-engine/plan.md:35:| **Cutover mechanism** | Fenced compare-and-swap on the P4a activation manifest; byte-identical `manifest.serving-prior.json` retained for rollback |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/011-runtime-engine/plan.md:40:P4b adds the runtime consumer P4a left out, as three small modules. `compiled-route.cjs` is an archetype-adaptive pure engine: given `(hubId, taskText)` it loads the hub's compiled snapshot and routes it through the child's own engine — `evaluateCanary` or `evaluateRoute`, by archetype — returning a normalized decision and deferring on off-signal prompts. `resolve.cjs` is the safety gate: it serves the compiled decision only when the runtime flag is set and the hub's manifest reads `servingAuthority: compiled`, fails safe to null on any error, and exposes a `--hub/--prompt` CLI front-door. `flip-serving.cjs` is the operated switch: a fenced CAS that moves a hub `legacy → compiled` behind a P4a-binding check, a green canary, the frozen-scorer pin, and a live-route proof, retaining a byte-identical pre-flip manifest so `--rollback` is byte-exact. The path was proven on `sk-code`, then the cutover was executed across all seven hubs — each live `SKILL.md` wired with an additive flag-gated directive, recompiled with archetype-adaptive re-certification, and flipped `legacy → compiled` — held inert behind the default-off `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING` flag with a byte-exact rollback retained per hub.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/011-runtime-engine/plan.md:46:<!-- ANCHOR:quality-gates -->
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/011-runtime-engine/plan.md:47:## 2. QUALITY GATES
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/011-runtime-engine/plan.md:50:- [x] Each hub's rollout child exposes `harness/build-artifacts.cjs` (`loadSnapshot`) and `lib/canary-router.cjs` (`evaluateCanary`).
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/011-runtime-engine/plan.md:51:- [x] Each hub is P4a-bound: `010-live-activation/activation/<hub>/manifest.json` carries the compiled generation as `selectedPolicy`.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/011-runtime-engine/plan.md:55:- [x] The compiled-route engine reuses each child's archetype engine — `evaluateCanary` or `evaluateRoute` — (no reimplemented routing algebra) and defers on off-signal prompts.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/011-runtime-engine/plan.md:56:- [x] The resolver is double-gated and fail-safe; inert with the flag off; CLI prints the compiled decision or a legacy sentinel.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/011-runtime-engine/plan.md:57:- [x] The flip is a fenced CAS behind four green gates with a byte-exact rollback and a `serving-flip-record.json`.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/011-runtime-engine/plan.md:59:- [x] Per-hub live-`SKILL.md` routing directive wired to the resolver (complete: each of the 7 hubs carries an additive, flag-gated compiled-routing directive).
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/011-runtime-engine/plan.md:60:- [x] Seven-hub `legacy → compiled` serving flip complete (all 7 flipped, inert behind the default-off flag); post-flip real-model re-verification treated as satisfied by the P4a T9 result plus flag-off inertness.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/011-runtime-engine/plan.md:62:<!-- /ANCHOR:quality-gates -->
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/011-runtime-engine/plan.md:71:Consume-then-serve, gated. A pure engine consumes the compiled contract by reusing the proven canary engine; a resolver decides authority through two independent gates; an operated fenced-CAS flip changes that authority per hub. Authority is data on the activation manifest, never a property of the engine itself — so shipping the engine changes nothing until a hub is both flipped and flagged on.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/011-runtime-engine/plan.md:74:- **`lib/compiled-route.cjs`**: archetype-adaptive pure runtime engine. Maps each hub to its rollout child, loads `{ snapshot } = loadSnapshot()` and the child's archetype engine (`evaluateCanary` or `evaluateRoute`), routes `taskText`, and normalizes the result to `{hubId, action, selectionKind, targets, effectivePolicyHash, generation}`. Caches per-hub engines; side-effect-free.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/011-runtime-engine/plan.md:75:- **`lib/resolve.cjs`**: serving resolver + CLI. `resolveRoute(hubId, taskText)` returns the compiled decision only when `flagEnabled()` and `servingAuthority(hubId) === 'compiled'`; else null. Reads `010-live-activation/activation/<hub>/manifest.json`. Fails safe (try/catch → null). CLI: `--hub <id> --prompt <text>`.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/011-runtime-engine/plan.md:76:- **`lib/flip-serving.cjs`**: per-hub serving flip. Fenced CAS on the activation manifest (`legacy → compiled`, `shadowOnly true → false`); gates on P4a-binding, `validate-canary.cjs`, pinned scorer digests, and `assertEngineRoutes` (≥1 designed scenario). Retains `manifest.serving-prior.json`; `--rollback`; emits `serving-flip-record.json`.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/011-runtime-engine/plan.md:80:Prompt → `resolveRoute(hubId, taskText)` → gate 1 flag (`SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING=1`) and gate 2 manifest (`servingAuthority: compiled`) → on pass, `compiledRoute` loads the hub's rollout-child engine and routes via its archetype engine (`evaluateCanary` or `evaluateRoute`) → normalized decision returned; on any miss or error, null → caller keeps the legacy prose smart-router. The flip path is operated out-of-band: `flip-serving.cjs` proves the four gates, retains the pre-flip manifest, swaps `servingAuthority` and advances the fence, and records `serving-flip-record.json`.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/011-runtime-engine/plan.md:89:This phase introduces the first runtime consumer of the compiled contract and an operated serving switch, so the surface inventory is required before the flip runs.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/011-runtime-engine/plan.md:93:| Rollout child engines (`harness/build-artifacts.cjs`, `lib/canary-router.cjs`) | Proven compiled snapshot + canary algebra | Reused read-only by the engine | The engine defines no routing algebra; children stay byte-unchanged |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/011-runtime-engine/plan.md:94:| P4a activation manifest (`010-live-activation/activation/<hub>/manifest.json`) | Bound `selectedPolicy`; now `servingAuthority: compiled` (post-flip) | Read by the resolver; CAS target of the flip | Flip asserted compiled `selectedPolicy` and retained a byte-identical serving-prior; all 7 now read `compiled` |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/011-runtime-engine/plan.md:96:| Runtime flag `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING` | Off by default | Read by the resolver | Flag off ⇒ resolver returns null everywhere (inert) |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/011-runtime-engine/plan.md:97:| Live `SKILL.md` (per hub) | Authoritative serving routing | **Wired — additive, flag-gated compiled-routing directive added** | Each of the 7 hubs' `SKILL.md` shells to the resolver front-door under `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING=1`, self-gating on serving authority; existing prose routing unchanged |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/011-runtime-engine/plan.md:101:- Binding: confirm each target hub's manifest `selectedPolicy` is the compiled generation (P4a-bound).
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/011-runtime-engine/plan.md:103:- Inertness: with the flag off, confirm the resolver returns null / a legacy sentinel for a compiled-serving hub.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/011-runtime-engine/plan.md:109:<!-- ANCHOR:phases -->
