.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/011-runtime-engine/plan.md:112:### Phase 1: Setup
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/011-runtime-engine/plan.md:113:- [x] Author `lib/compiled-route.cjs` — map hubs to rollout children, load `loadSnapshot`/`evaluateCanary`, normalize the decision, cache per-hub engines.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/011-runtime-engine/plan.md:115:- [x] Author `lib/resolve.cjs` — double gate (flag + manifest), fail-safe null, `--hub/--prompt` CLI front-door.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/011-runtime-engine/plan.md:117:### Phase 2: Core Implementation
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/011-runtime-engine/plan.md:118:- [x] Author `lib/flip-serving.cjs` — fenced CAS `legacy → compiled`, gates on P4a-binding, `validate-canary.cjs`, pinned scorer digests, and `assertEngineRoutes`.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/011-runtime-engine/plan.md:119:- [x] Retain a byte-identical `manifest.serving-prior.json` before the swap; advance the monotonic fence epoch; emit `serving-flip-record.json`.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/011-runtime-engine/plan.md:120:- [x] Implement `--rollback` (restore the byte-identical serving-prior, advance the fence) and the `ALREADY-COMPILED` idempotent no-op.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/011-runtime-engine/plan.md:122:### Phase 3: Verification
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/011-runtime-engine/plan.md:123:- [x] Prove end-to-end on `sk-code`: flip → `servingAuthority: compiled` (green gates) → front-door returns `action: route` (flag on) and a legacy sentinel (flag off) → byte-exact `--rollback` to legacy.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/011-runtime-engine/plan.md:124:- [x] Confirm the frozen scorer digests are unchanged after the proof; `sk-code` was then flipped for the cutover (`compiled`, byte-exact-reversible via the retained serving-prior).
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/011-runtime-engine/plan.md:125:- [x] Wire each hub's `SKILL.md` routing directive to the resolver and flip all seven hubs `legacy → compiled` (complete, inert behind the default-off flag); post-flip real-model re-verification treated as satisfied by the P4a T9 result plus flag-off inertness.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/011-runtime-engine/plan.md:127:<!-- /ANCHOR:phases -->
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/011-runtime-engine/plan.md:136:| Reuse-integrity | Engine routes via the child's `evaluateCanary` (no forked algebra) | Route a signal-bearing prompt; compare against the child's canary decision |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/011-runtime-engine/plan.md:137:| Gating | Flag off / manifest legacy ⇒ inert; both on ⇒ served | `resolve.cjs --hub … --prompt …` with `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING` on and off |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/011-runtime-engine/plan.md:138:| Reversibility | Byte-exact rollback per hub | `flip-serving.cjs --hub … --rollback` (`restoredHash` = pre-flip serving-prior) |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/011-runtime-engine/plan.md:139:| Flip preconditions | P4a-binding, canary green, scorer frozen, engine routes ≥1 scenario | The four gates in `flip-serving.cjs`; a failing gate aborts before any write |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/011-runtime-engine/plan.md:140:| Manual (satisfied) | Post-flip real-model routing per hub | Satisfied by the P4a T9 result (LUNA / SOL / MiniMax, 0 wrong-hub routes) plus flag-off inertness — routing is byte-identical, so the flag changes hashes only |
