.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/011-runtime-engine/checklist.md:67:- [x] CHK-023 [P0] The serving flip aborts before any write when a gate fails.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/011-runtime-engine/checklist.md:68:  - **Evidence**: `flip-serving.cjs` aborts on non-P4a-binding, a non-zero `validate-canary.cjs`, a scorer-digest mismatch, or `assertEngineRoutes` routing zero scenarios.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/011-runtime-engine/checklist.md:69:- [x] CHK-024 [P0] Byte-exact rollback is proven on `sk-code` and retained.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/011-runtime-engine/checklist.md:70:  - **Evidence**: `--rollback` restores `manifest.serving-prior.json` byte-for-byte (the retained serving-prior reads `servingAuthority: legacy`, `shadowOnly: true`); the mechanism was exercised and proven. `sk-code` was then flipped for the production cutover and is currently `servingAuthority: compiled` at fence epoch 4, with the byte-identical serving-prior retained so the same byte-exact rollback remains available.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/011-runtime-engine/checklist.md:71:- [x] CHK-025 [P1] The flip is idempotent.
