   160	<!-- ANCHOR:risks -->
   161	## 6. RISKS & DEPENDENCIES
   162	
   163	| Type | Item | Impact | Mitigation |
   164	|------|------|--------|------------|
   165	| Risk | Premise capture — treating default-on as a switch | Flips an undocumented flag that inverts the kill-switch for zero routing benefit | This decision reframes default-on as a P4 outcome gated on P0–P3; the flip is never this phase's action |
   166	| Risk | Silent drift normalized as "compiled" | A drifted hub serves legacy while dashboards claim compiled | P1 drift-CI fails re-mint-required; P0 observability distinguishes drifted from broken |
   167	| Risk | Duplicated allowlist diverges | `COMPILED_ROUTING_HUBS` and `HUB_CHILD` drift apart, mis-gating hubs | P3 single-sources eligibility to "valid fresh manifest exists"; both predicates derive from it |
   168	| Risk | Runtime resolver coupled to a spec-tree path | A spec renumber breaks all compiled routing to the sentinel | REQ-005 P0 remediation: promote the resolver to a stable runtime path or document the coupling as a named drift source with a guard |
   169	| Dependency | Frozen benchmark scorer (three pinned files) | Any edit invalidates the parity baseline the whole program rests on | Restated as a hard pin per migration step; never edited |
   170	| Dependency | Sibling `013`/`014` alignment phases | Onboarding (create-skill) and validation (benchmarks) must consume this phase's contracts | REQ-007 cross-links; the contracts live here once and are referenced, not restated |
   171	
   172	<!-- /ANCHOR:risks -->
   173	
   174	---
   175	
   176	<!-- ANCHOR:questions -->
   177	## 7. NON-FUNCTIONAL REQUIREMENTS
   178	
   179	### Reversibility
   180	- **NFR-R01**: Every step P0→P4 names an explicit rollback; the P4 global default-on keeps `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING=0` as the documented, load-bearing kill-switch.
   181	- **NFR-R02**: Because compiled routing is byte-identical to legacy for matched hubs, any step's rollback is behavior-neutral by construction, not merely by test.
   182	
   183	### Determinism
   184	- **NFR-D01**: The fallback is deterministic: identical (hub config, manifest, flag) inputs always yield the same served-authority; drift is a pure function of a hash mismatch, not timing.
   185	
   186	### Authority
   187	- **NFR-A01**: Serving authority is conferred only by a valid, fresh manifest under an enabled flag for an eligible hub; nothing else grants it, and the eligibility predicate has exactly one source of truth (P3).
   188	
   189	---
   190	
   130	| Surface | Current Role | Planned Action | Verification |
   131	|---------|--------------|----------------|--------------|
   132	| `ENV-REFERENCE.md` | Source of truth for environment defaults | Document the flag, current default, explicit enablement, and `=0` kill-switch | Documentation lint plus runtime default/override probes |
   133	| Verify harness | Treats fallback outcomes without enough cause detail | Add drift-vs-breakage classification and a per-hub status readout | Fresh, stale, missing, and broken fixtures |
   134	| Runtime resolver/front door | Reads a resolver beneath the spec tree | Promote the resolver to a stable runtime path, or guard and document the coupling if promotion is rejected | Spec-tree move simulation and fail-safe fallback check |
   135	| CI | Does not enforce manifest freshness | Add live-hash versus minted-digest comparison | Positive fresh case and negative re-mint-required case |
   136	| Environment profiles | Repository default remains off | Enable one named canary profile only | Profile-specific flag assertion; all other profiles remain off |
   137	| Eligibility consumers | Two hand-maintained hub sets | Derive both from the single manifest-freshness predicate | Consumer parity and no-manifest legacy case |
   138	| Hub directives and runtime defaults | Seven additive directives, default-off predicate | Stage P4 changes in lockstep, one hub at a time | Per-hub route parity, status readout, and `=0` rollback |
   139	| Frozen scorer files | Stable route-gold baseline | Read and hash only; never edit | Before/after digest equality per stage |
   140	
   141	Required inventories before implementation:
   142	
   143	- Locate every read of `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING` and every environment profile that can set it.
   144	- Locate both current eligibility sets and every caller that assumes their shape.
   145	- Record all seven hub directives and their exact fallback behavior.
   146	- Record the resolver's current spec-tree dependency before choosing promotion or an explicit guard.
   147	<!-- /ANCHOR:affected-surfaces -->
